Rudzani Matshili The cast and band of Freedom The Musical, a new groundbreaking musical is hard at rehearsals at the State Theatre ahead of the opening of the show about a TUT student and leader of fees must fall movement played by Simphiwe Ndlovu,25. A strong cast of 47 members and a thirteen piece band tell the story of Phindile’s life which takes a sharp turn after the students’ protest at the Union Buildings in Pretoria. This story is a testament to her determination to triumph regardless of the odds stacked against her by the system as well as society. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
