    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  “The character is challenging as I have to wrap my head around everything that Phindi has to represent, because she’s literally found in every scene and she has to be the voice for  everyone,” she said. Directed by multi-award winning playwright Aubrey Sekhabi, it features Hip Hop star Simphele ‘PdotO’ Mnyandu, Kabelo “Bonafide Billi” Togoe, Motswako rapper Chad da Don, the experienced baritone Otto Maidi and 2017 Idols top ten finalist Thokozile Ndimande to highlight a few.